    <h1>Color Meanings and Their HTML Codes</h1>

    <div class="color-box red">
        <strong>Red</strong>: Represents passion, energy, love, and danger. Often used for warnings or errors.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box green">
        <strong>Green</strong>: Symbolizes nature, growth, calmness, and health. Commonly used for success messages.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box blue">
        <strong>Blue</strong>: Represents trust, stability, peace, and professionalism. Often used for links and corporate themes.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box yellow">
        <strong>Yellow</strong>: Represents happiness, caution, and optimism. Often used to grab attention or for warnings.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box purple">
        <strong>Purple</strong>: Associated with royalty, luxury, creativity, and spirituality.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box orange">
        <strong>Orange</strong>: Represents enthusiasm, warmth, and excitement. Frequently used for calls to action.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box black">
        <strong>Black</strong>: Represents sophistication, elegance, mystery, and power. Common for formal or minimalistic designs.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box white">
        <strong>White</strong>: Symbolizes purity, clarity, simplicity, and freshness. Often used for clean designs and backgrounds.
    </div>
    <div class="color-box gray">
        <strong>Gray</strong>: Represents neutrality, balance, and professionalism. Commonly used for secondary information and backgrounds.
    </div>

